WEBVTT

00:06.506 --> 00:08.425
[opening theme music playing]

00:49.299 --> 00:51.968
STILL SHINING

00:56.556 --> 00:58.016
[Eun-a] <i>Please let me say goodbye</i>

00:59.809 --> 01:01.936
<i>to Tae-seo in person before I go.</i>

01:06.524 --> 01:09.027
<i>I know you guys don't come out</i>
<i>when it gets cold.</i>

01:10.612 --> 01:11.446
<i>But still…</i>

01:13.698 --> 01:14.866
[Tae-seo] Mo Eun-a.

01:17.285 --> 01:18.703
[slow instrumental music plays]

01:28.797 --> 01:35.428
STILL SHINING

01:40.225 --> 01:44.354
[exclaims] All the places in this town
look the same no matter how far you go.

01:45.563 --> 01:47.232
Are we even getting close?

01:51.486 --> 01:53.488
[emotional music playing]

01:54.864 --> 01:56.741
The fireflies…

01:56.825 --> 02:00.036
[hesitates] I know they don't come out
when it's cold, but…

02:00.120 --> 02:01.079
[Tae-seo] What are you…

02:03.414 --> 02:05.333
doing here?

02:13.508 --> 02:15.051
[Hyeong-seok] Hey, isn't that Tae-seo?

02:15.969 --> 02:16.803
Tae-seo!

02:21.724 --> 02:23.017
Im A-sol, get out.

02:24.769 --> 02:26.396
Tae-seo, you drive instead!

02:26.479 --> 02:28.565
You know where the restaurant is!

02:28.648 --> 02:30.108
The road here is really confusing!

02:30.191 --> 02:31.234
I'm tired!

02:32.735 --> 02:33.862
[Hyeong-seok grunts]

02:33.945 --> 02:35.488
I drove all the way here!

02:35.572 --> 02:37.407
I'm so tired!

02:38.658 --> 02:39.659
[Hyeong-seok grunts]

02:40.618 --> 02:42.287
Who is he talking with?

02:46.791 --> 02:48.376
I'm cold!

02:49.460 --> 02:50.420
Come on.

02:51.421 --> 02:53.631
[Hyeong-seok grunts] Gosh.

03:02.098 --> 03:03.725
[Hyeong-seok] He hasn't changed one bit.

03:04.309 --> 03:06.019
I used to take really good care of him.

03:06.102 --> 03:07.520
People thought he was my brother.

03:07.604 --> 03:09.689
He looks more like me, not Tae-seo.

03:09.772 --> 03:12.984
What are you talking about?
He's clearly a cuter version of Tae-seo.

03:13.067 --> 03:14.694
I get that a lot.

03:15.528 --> 03:16.738
We just have different vibes.

03:16.821 --> 03:18.281
A-sol, let me pour you a glass.

03:18.364 --> 03:20.158
Thank you for inviting us.

03:20.241 --> 03:22.619
-[Hyeong-seok] It looks delicious.
-[Hui-seo] Right?

03:22.702 --> 03:26.497
They have the best seafood <i>ramyeon</i>
and aged kimchi here.

03:26.581 --> 03:29.500
They only bring out
the aged kimchi for me. [chuckles]

03:30.001 --> 03:32.921
[groans softly] Tae-seo left Seoul
right away for your sake.

03:33.004 --> 03:34.672
He didn't hesitate at all. [scoffs]

03:34.756 --> 03:36.215
Now that I'm here, I can see why.

03:36.299 --> 03:38.343
When he was in Seoul,
he always looked so worn out.

03:38.426 --> 03:40.303
But here, the ocean's right there,

03:40.386 --> 03:42.013
the sky's clear, and the air's fresh.

03:43.306 --> 03:45.266
Man, it's nice here.

03:46.309 --> 03:48.102
Wait, so that's what you meant.

03:48.186 --> 03:50.647
"My dad looks at the sky at work,

03:50.730 --> 03:52.690
and my mom looks
at the sky and ocean at work."

03:52.774 --> 03:55.068
He said it was the best job
in the universe.

03:55.944 --> 03:58.029
-That's what Mom used to say.
-[gentle music playing]

03:58.112 --> 03:59.447
You still remember it, Tae-seo?

03:59.530 --> 04:01.616
[Hyeong-seok] Of course, he does.

04:01.699 --> 04:04.285
Man, you were on crutches
the last time I saw you.

04:04.369 --> 04:05.828
You walk so well now. I'm proud.

04:05.912 --> 04:09.374
-Come on. That's ancient history. [laughs]
-[Hyeong-seok laughs]

04:09.457 --> 04:12.293
-[Hui-seo] Is your dad doing well?
-[Hyeong-seok] More than well.

04:12.377 --> 04:14.128
Hey, come on.

04:14.212 --> 04:16.130
You need to drive us back to Seoul.

04:16.214 --> 04:17.715
I need to visit the hospital.

04:17.799 --> 04:18.800
[Hui-seo] Tae-seo.

04:19.550 --> 04:20.385
Just go.

04:21.052 --> 04:24.180
Your guests came all the way here.
You should take them back to Seoul.

04:24.264 --> 04:26.641
Even Hyeong-seok's here,
and he never comes.

04:26.724 --> 04:28.518
You're making it awkward for him to drink.

04:28.601 --> 04:32.438
[Hyeong-seok] Did you miss me that much,
my little brother? Have a drink.

04:32.522 --> 04:34.357
You can even drink now.
You're all grown up.

04:34.440 --> 04:35.483
[Hui-seo] Oh, come on.

04:42.156 --> 04:44.701
The lights on the bicycle were broken.

04:46.327 --> 04:48.621
The girl on the bicycle earlier
was your ex, right?

04:54.294 --> 04:55.545
So she lives in Gangneung.

04:56.629 --> 04:57.463
She doesn't.

05:00.008 --> 05:01.301
Then, where does she live?

05:02.343 --> 05:03.511
I don't know.

05:05.096 --> 05:06.306
Why did she come here?

05:08.224 --> 05:09.892
I don't know.

05:09.976 --> 05:11.644
[A-sol] So you didn't get to talk to her.

05:13.021 --> 05:15.732
You must be frustrated and curious.

05:22.280 --> 05:24.282
[music continues playing]

05:41.340 --> 05:43.885
MO EUN-A

05:44.469 --> 05:46.262
MO EUN-A

05:48.765 --> 05:50.767
[Tae-seo] <i>Why were you in Yeonwoo…</i>

06:03.696 --> 06:05.698
[music fades]

06:08.409 --> 06:09.744
[camera shutter clicking]

06:12.789 --> 06:13.790
[sighs]

06:33.392 --> 06:35.144
Tae-seo's here.

06:37.105 --> 06:38.397
Yes, I'm here.

06:40.358 --> 06:42.652
You must be having such a hard time.

06:43.736 --> 06:47.740
Get plenty of rest
while you're on leave from the military.

06:52.370 --> 06:53.287
[Hui-seo] What's this?

06:54.330 --> 06:55.915
At least tell me if you're coming.

06:55.998 --> 06:57.500
I didn't even eat before I came here.

06:58.209 --> 07:00.211
Did you get to talk with Grandma?

07:01.462 --> 07:03.381
She talked about
when I was in the military.

07:03.464 --> 07:05.508
She'd always talk about
my middle school days.

07:05.591 --> 07:06.884
Time must've passed for her.

07:10.680 --> 07:13.057
Have you seen Eun-a
from the house at the end?

07:13.850 --> 07:15.268
Why suddenly mention that name?

07:17.103 --> 07:17.937
I thought I saw her.

07:19.230 --> 07:21.607
[smacks lips]
I don't want you being pathetic.

07:22.733 --> 07:26.821
[inhales sharply] Live an ordinary life.
Get married and have kids.

07:26.904 --> 07:29.407
Come visit from time to time.
Is that too much to ask?

07:29.490 --> 07:30.741
I'm going to live alone,

07:30.825 --> 07:34.078
and then send our grandparents off
to be with Mom and Dad.

07:34.162 --> 07:35.163
I'll do all of that.

07:35.246 --> 07:36.247
Did you see her or not?

07:37.123 --> 07:38.541
You didn't even answer me.

07:39.584 --> 07:40.918
I'm off.

07:52.930 --> 07:55.433
[bus door hydraulics hissing]

08:05.318 --> 08:06.444
[hesitates] Hold on, please.

08:11.282 --> 08:14.202
[bus door hydraulics hissing]

08:19.582 --> 08:22.793
Eun-a should be here by now,
but she's late.

08:22.877 --> 08:25.338
She went out with that old, beat-up bike.

08:26.214 --> 08:28.049
You need to hurry and find her.

08:29.634 --> 08:30.885
[hesitates] Right.

08:33.221 --> 08:35.223
[melancholic music playing]

09:13.094 --> 09:14.095
[sniffles]

09:17.306 --> 09:18.349
[camera shutter clicks]

09:26.482 --> 09:27.692
[sniffles]

09:46.294 --> 09:48.296
[music fades]

10:03.185 --> 10:04.312
[sighs heavily]

10:24.749 --> 10:26.751
[gentle music playing]

11:14.423 --> 11:16.425
[music fades]

11:16.509 --> 11:17.760
What are you doing here?

11:17.843 --> 11:20.513
I came to take
a quick look around our school.

11:21.347 --> 11:22.681
I had no idea it had closed down.

11:23.349 --> 11:26.977
Not that. Why here? In Yeonwoo.

11:29.647 --> 11:31.065
Are you staying here for good?

11:32.233 --> 11:33.484
No, just for a bit.

11:36.195 --> 11:37.780
I'm going to stay with Park So-hyeon.

11:40.324 --> 11:41.659
This is great.

11:41.742 --> 11:44.328
Even though I was worried
about running into you here,

11:44.412 --> 11:48.416
I still wanted to tell you
that I was leaving to live with So-hyeon.

11:50.292 --> 11:51.627
I wanted to say a quick goodbye

11:52.753 --> 11:54.547
and tell you in person too.

11:56.424 --> 11:57.508
And now, I got to do that.

11:59.427 --> 12:01.387
My bicycle lights are broken.

12:01.470 --> 12:03.806
You can follow me from behind then.

12:04.890 --> 12:06.434
This is great.

12:06.517 --> 12:08.936
I was worried
I'd have to push my bicycle back.

12:09.019 --> 12:11.689
Remember the fork in the road
where we always used to split up?

12:12.356 --> 12:13.899
Let's say goodbye there.

12:14.608 --> 12:16.652
I really wanted to do this with you.

12:18.154 --> 12:18.988
This is great.

12:21.574 --> 12:22.658
When are you leaving?

12:23.325 --> 12:24.326
Soon.

12:26.745 --> 12:27.830
Since we've met,

12:29.206 --> 12:30.291
let's say goodbye.

12:31.459 --> 12:33.502
I really wanted to do that with you.

12:35.463 --> 12:36.839
Bye, then.

12:39.717 --> 12:40.885
I'm off.

12:42.094 --> 12:44.138
[emotional music playing]

13:11.499 --> 13:12.500
[brakes screech]

13:43.280 --> 13:45.282
[music fades]

14:12.810 --> 14:14.395
[sighs heavily]

14:16.188 --> 14:18.190
[dramatic music playing]

14:58.397 --> 15:00.399
[music fades]

15:02.860 --> 15:04.320
[line ringing]

15:14.830 --> 15:15.831
It's me.

15:19.084 --> 15:20.252
I know.

15:23.130 --> 15:24.673
Nothing happened, right?

15:26.342 --> 15:27.718
<i>I…</i>

15:27.801 --> 15:31.430
<i>I left you alone</i>
<i>with that colleague of yours.</i>

15:33.474 --> 15:35.809
It didn't cause trouble for you, right?

15:37.978 --> 15:39.146
[Eun-a]<i> Why…</i>

15:40.189 --> 15:42.107
[voice breaking]
Why are you worried about me?

15:44.360 --> 15:45.819
There's no need.

15:48.447 --> 15:50.115
<i>You had absolutely</i>

15:52.117 --> 15:53.702
nothing to worry about.

15:55.204 --> 15:57.039
[somber music playing]

15:57.122 --> 15:58.499
There was no need…

16:00.000 --> 16:01.001
<i>I guess so.</i>

16:01.877 --> 16:05.005
<i>I can still picture that field</i>
<i>in my mind clearly,</i>

16:06.256 --> 16:08.425
so I wondered
if you'd finished things properly.

16:10.636 --> 16:13.806
I wondered if leaving a place
you had poured your heart and soul into

16:14.932 --> 16:16.475
wasn't too hard on you.

16:19.061 --> 16:21.188
<i>I wondered why you were</i>
<i>always forced to leave</i>

16:22.731 --> 16:24.984
<i>when you never wanted to.</i>

16:27.653 --> 16:28.737
There was no need,

16:32.491 --> 16:35.119
but I kept wondering.

16:41.709 --> 16:43.544
Why is Park So-hyeon your mom?

16:43.627 --> 16:45.337
<i>Actually,</i>

16:45.421 --> 16:48.590
it's more that her mom is my grandmother.

16:50.217 --> 16:51.218
She's a good person.

16:51.927 --> 16:55.764
[Tae-seo] <i>You didn't make a bad decision</i>
<i>because you felt trapped, right?</i>

16:56.557 --> 16:59.685
-When you feel trapped--
<i>-</i>[Eun-a] <i>No, Tae-seo.</i>

17:03.105 --> 17:04.481
[Tae-seo] <i>I went to Tongyeong.</i>

17:05.232 --> 17:07.276
Your guesthouse was closed,

17:07.943 --> 17:09.903
<i>and I was told you had gone to your mom's.</i>

17:10.904 --> 17:13.741
<i>I thought it was the mom</i>
<i>who lives far away</i>

17:14.700 --> 17:16.410
and likes noodles.

17:17.786 --> 17:19.288
We missed each other.

17:19.872 --> 17:22.666
[sniffles] <i>We're really good at that.</i>

17:26.295 --> 17:28.297
OLD HOUSE IM A-SOL

17:33.635 --> 17:34.928
[doorbell rings]

17:39.016 --> 17:40.059
I should hang up.

17:40.142 --> 17:41.477
<i>Granny's going to wake up.</i>

17:41.560 --> 17:42.936
Bye.

17:45.230 --> 17:46.065
Eun…

17:54.490 --> 17:55.824
-[sighs]
-[music fades]

17:56.658 --> 18:00.621
Including meetings and a year-end party,
I had three events to attend.

18:00.704 --> 18:03.624
The venue was around here,
so I just stopped by.

18:07.127 --> 18:08.337
Were you drinking?

18:09.338 --> 18:11.006
Yeah, just a little.

18:12.466 --> 18:13.300
Sorry.

18:13.383 --> 18:16.303
[chuckles]
No need to apologize for drinking.

18:19.473 --> 18:20.516
Should I go?

18:21.100 --> 18:22.434
If you're tired, I'll go.

18:25.729 --> 18:26.980
Let's go out for a drink.

18:27.773 --> 18:29.108
I need to talk to you.

18:31.110 --> 18:32.069
Uh…

18:32.152 --> 18:34.613
I wanted to finish what we were watching.

18:35.906 --> 18:36.865
Sure.

18:39.827 --> 18:40.911
Um…

18:40.994 --> 18:42.746
I saw a <i>bungeoppang</i> place on the way here.

18:42.830 --> 18:44.498
But there was nowhere to park. [chuckles]

18:45.415 --> 18:46.291
I'll go buy you some.

18:50.003 --> 18:50.838
You can sit.

18:50.921 --> 18:51.755
Okay.

18:56.677 --> 18:59.096
[door lock beeps, chimes]

18:59.179 --> 19:00.889
[door opens, closes]

19:18.365 --> 19:19.575
[exhales]

19:27.082 --> 19:27.958
[A-sol] This is nice.

19:31.420 --> 19:35.799
It's nice to relax together like this
after a crazy day at work.

19:43.265 --> 19:44.266
Just one sip.

19:44.808 --> 19:46.268
I can leave my car here.

19:47.186 --> 19:48.395
[can hisses]

19:51.857 --> 19:52.941
[sighs in relief]

19:55.444 --> 19:56.278
Focus.

20:03.994 --> 20:06.121
[cellphone vibrating]

20:10.167 --> 20:13.337
HAE-JIN

20:14.338 --> 20:17.758
[Hae-jin] <i>Hi, Eun-a.</i>
<i>Sorry for calling you at this hour.</i>

20:17.841 --> 20:18.800
It's kind of urgent.

20:18.884 --> 20:20.969
Could you cover for me
for just three hours tomorrow?

20:21.553 --> 20:24.598
<i>You just need to check in</i>
<i>one guest at 3:00 p.m.</i>

20:46.995 --> 20:48.038
[Hae-jin exclaims]

20:48.121 --> 20:49.873
[panting]

20:49.957 --> 20:51.792
Gosh, sorry about the wait.

20:51.875 --> 20:53.627
There was just so much traffic today.

20:53.710 --> 20:56.380
Look at you dressed all properly
for just a few hours of work.

20:56.463 --> 20:58.131
You're such a professional.

20:58.215 --> 20:59.716
What do you want to eat?

20:59.800 --> 21:01.260
It's my treat, so let's go.

21:01.343 --> 21:03.220
I've got a bus to catch.

21:03.303 --> 21:05.138
Did you really just come to help me out?

21:05.889 --> 21:07.516
I'm touched.

21:08.558 --> 21:10.394
You sure you're not here to see someone?

21:13.605 --> 21:15.023
There is someone, right?

21:15.107 --> 21:18.110
[gasps] I knew it.
If you came to see them, you should.

21:24.324 --> 21:25.450
I did.

21:26.034 --> 21:27.369
[dramatic music playing]

21:27.452 --> 21:29.579
<i>Someone I wanted to see,</i>
<i>even for a moment.</i>

21:33.417 --> 21:34.418
I already saw him.

21:56.648 --> 22:01.153
YEON NAMSAN

22:30.557 --> 22:31.433
[Eun-a] <i>So-hyeon.</i>

22:32.726 --> 22:34.811
<i>I might arrive later than planned.</i>

22:35.437 --> 22:36.688
<i>I'll get back to you.</i>

23:26.488 --> 23:28.490
[music fades]

23:29.658 --> 23:31.660
[door lock beeping]

23:34.871 --> 23:36.706
[door lock chimes]

23:43.588 --> 23:45.590
[emotional music playing]

23:51.471 --> 23:53.098
[Eun-a]<i> This is where I stop.</i>

24:05.193 --> 24:07.988
<i>Trying to make things work,</i>

24:09.698 --> 24:11.950
<i>intruding into your peaceful life,</i>

24:13.827 --> 24:15.412
<i>and repeating this vicious cycle.</i>

24:15.495 --> 24:16.580
<i>Enough.</i>

24:22.544 --> 24:24.004
[cellphone vibrates]

24:27.591 --> 24:29.092
[So-hyeon] <i>Are you crazy?</i>

24:29.176 --> 24:32.262
<i>Do you know how much the fees would be</i>
<i>if you canceled your flight now?</i>

24:32.345 --> 24:34.306
<i>At the hotel you worked at ten years ago,</i>

24:34.389 --> 24:36.725
<i>your former coworker</i>
<i>is now the assistant manager.</i>

24:36.808 --> 24:40.145
<i>They're all waiting for you to come back,</i>

24:40.228 --> 24:41.897
<i>not to mention my mom.</i>

24:41.980 --> 24:43.982
<i>Everyone's waiting for you.</i>

24:46.693 --> 24:48.153
[Eun-a] <i>I'll go as planned.</i>

24:49.404 --> 24:51.656
<i>I'll keep my promise.</i>

24:55.327 --> 24:56.578
<i>Dad.</i>

24:56.661 --> 25:00.373
<i>When you told me to live freely,</i>
<i>as if I was on a journey,</i>

25:01.249 --> 25:04.544
<i>you meant that in life,</i>
<i>we can't stay even when we want to.</i>

25:05.128 --> 25:07.255
<i>Things seem like they'll last forever,</i>
<i>but they don't.</i>

25:09.549 --> 25:12.135
<i>And since life is full of such things,</i>

25:12.219 --> 25:14.054
<i>when it's time to leave,</i>

25:14.804 --> 25:17.349
<i>you meant I should just take off,</i>
<i>as if I was on a journey.</i>

25:20.435 --> 25:24.731
<i>Now at age 30, I finally understand this.</i>

25:34.449 --> 25:37.118
MISSED CALL
EUN-A

25:38.787 --> 25:40.789
[music fades]

25:45.126 --> 25:46.711
[door opens]

25:46.795 --> 25:48.672
MART

25:52.384 --> 25:53.218
It's cold outside.

25:58.306 --> 25:59.391
[Eun-a] Ah…

26:00.850 --> 26:02.018
Give me one second.

26:18.994 --> 26:21.371
[inside door opens, closes]

26:41.933 --> 26:46.646
[Eun-a] <i>When my dad and I first came here,</i>
<i>we had just one bag with us.</i>

26:47.397 --> 26:49.274
<i>It's in the main bedroom dresser.</i>

26:49.357 --> 26:51.067
<i>It should be in the bottom drawer.</i>

26:51.151 --> 26:53.361
<i>It's a backpack that you use for hiking.</i>

26:54.821 --> 26:57.198
<i>Can you get it for me?</i>

27:05.290 --> 27:06.541
[coughs, sniffles]

27:07.375 --> 27:08.376
[objects clatter]

27:09.419 --> 27:11.129
[footsteps approaching]

27:17.594 --> 27:19.137
Is this the one?

27:19.220 --> 27:20.680
Yeah, it is.

27:24.434 --> 27:26.227
This should be enough to take with me.

27:27.103 --> 27:29.856
I thought I wouldn't be able
to take anything from here.

27:29.939 --> 27:31.399
But I got something thanks to you.

27:34.778 --> 27:36.821
You've never been
in our kitchen before, right?

27:36.905 --> 27:38.490
This is the best part of our house.

27:38.573 --> 27:40.742
I'm sure you didn't call
to show me your kitchen.

27:43.578 --> 27:45.997
I went to Seoul
because I had something to do.

27:46.748 --> 27:49.042
And since it's Seoul,
Yeon Namsan was right there…

27:49.918 --> 27:51.544
I thought of you, so I called.

27:54.089 --> 27:55.757
I called without even thinking,

27:56.841 --> 27:58.426
but now that I see you here,

27:58.510 --> 28:00.095
I think I know why I did that.

28:01.638 --> 28:04.265
I guess I wanted to do this with you.

28:08.395 --> 28:09.604
Let's go over there.

28:21.991 --> 28:23.368
This is yours.

28:34.963 --> 28:37.215
I finally got to offer you some tea.

28:43.179 --> 28:44.305
I'm…

28:46.307 --> 28:48.184
leaving on Friday.

28:49.728 --> 28:50.770
Mmm.

28:52.355 --> 28:53.273
That's pretty soon.

29:04.743 --> 29:07.912
You were right. I felt trapped,
so Park So-hyeon became my mom.

29:10.206 --> 29:12.500
That's what it took for me to allow that.

29:16.796 --> 29:18.506
But to put it differently,

29:19.924 --> 29:22.010
I was able to make up my mind
thanks to you.

29:23.386 --> 29:25.388
[gentle music playing]

29:25.889 --> 29:29.350
I'd been thinking for a while
that maybe I should accept her as family.

29:29.976 --> 29:33.313
My dad at least left me Park So-hyeon
before he left.

29:34.105 --> 29:35.398
That's how I see it now.

29:38.067 --> 29:39.569
I'm saying it's not your fault.

29:40.612 --> 29:41.821
It's thanks to you.

29:43.198 --> 29:45.033
That's how I've always felt about you.

29:48.536 --> 29:50.163
It's all thanks to you in the end.

29:51.331 --> 29:54.501
But you probably feel
the exact opposite about me.

29:55.710 --> 29:56.753
If you go…

29:59.130 --> 30:00.423
will you come back?

30:00.507 --> 30:02.091
[Eun-a] Right now,

30:02.675 --> 30:04.302
I don't plan to.

30:07.096 --> 30:08.556
Where will you be living?

30:08.640 --> 30:12.060
[Eun-a] At Park So-hyeon's mom's place.
The lady who'll become my grandmother.

30:12.143 --> 30:13.478
They don't live together.

30:13.561 --> 30:14.437
What about work?

30:14.521 --> 30:16.564
I can work right away too.

30:18.733 --> 30:20.527
Park So-hyeon told me

30:20.610 --> 30:24.113
the hotel I worked at ten years ago
is waiting for me to return,

30:25.824 --> 30:26.825
so I should go.

30:27.951 --> 30:31.287
It's kind of amazing
that they still remember me.

30:31.371 --> 30:32.622
I liked it there.

30:33.414 --> 30:34.374
But…

30:35.708 --> 30:37.418
If I hadn't gone there…

30:42.841 --> 30:44.092
If I hadn't left…

30:47.762 --> 30:50.056
That's all I kept thinking about
for the past ten years.

30:53.893 --> 30:55.979
But I think I can finally go back now.

31:02.110 --> 31:03.611
You'll have a place to stay,

31:04.779 --> 31:06.281
your grandmother will be there,

31:07.115 --> 31:08.741
and you'll have a job.

31:17.041 --> 31:17.959
Why…

31:19.085 --> 31:20.879
did you go to Tongyeong?

31:22.714 --> 31:26.342
I couldn't understand
why things were like this between us.

31:29.429 --> 31:30.680
Everything felt wrong.

31:31.723 --> 31:33.558
[Eun-a] You had every reason to do that.

31:34.767 --> 31:36.895
My decision when I was 20 was wrong,

31:38.313 --> 31:39.397
but yours was right.

31:42.400 --> 31:43.234
[sighs softly]

31:47.322 --> 31:48.448
Do you realize

31:48.531 --> 31:50.867
we're worried about each other right now?

31:52.201 --> 31:53.286
Because for us,

31:54.621 --> 31:56.289
we can't make things hard for each other.

31:58.541 --> 32:00.043
No matter where we are.

32:05.673 --> 32:07.634
You're the only one
in the world who's like that.

32:11.763 --> 32:13.765
[music fades]

32:13.848 --> 32:16.976
I told you I logged into your account
and listened to music twice.

32:18.269 --> 32:19.520
Both times happened here.

32:26.069 --> 32:27.904
PLAYLIST

32:27.987 --> 32:29.739
[Eun-a] <i>It was December.</i>

32:29.822 --> 32:31.157
[melancholic music builds]

32:31.240 --> 32:33.785
I had caught a cold after shoveling
all the snow in the village.

32:33.868 --> 32:35.286
[sniffles, sighs]

32:35.370 --> 32:37.455
<i>I had decided on interning in Hawaii.</i>

32:41.000 --> 32:43.920
<i>And I had finally accepted</i>
<i>that we broke up.</i>

32:44.671 --> 32:46.714
[melancholic music playing]

32:46.798 --> 32:51.094
<i>Then, when I gave up on everything</i>
<i>in Tongyeong and came here,</i>

32:51.678 --> 32:53.179
<i>even before leaving for Seoul</i>…

32:55.723 --> 32:57.642
<i>When I logged into your account…</i>

32:57.725 --> 32:59.560
[knocking on door]

33:00.853 --> 33:01.813
Look at me.

33:03.064 --> 33:06.609
[Eun-a] <i>…it felt like</i>
<i>I was looking at you.</i>

33:10.363 --> 33:11.698
Even when I'm far away,

33:12.907 --> 33:16.119
if I need to borrow your strength,
I'm logging into your account.

33:17.996 --> 33:19.247
You don't mind, right?

33:21.416 --> 33:22.375
If you go there,

33:24.335 --> 33:25.378
will you smile like that?

33:30.633 --> 33:32.385
[Eun-a] I don't like her.

33:34.429 --> 33:37.015
She's so cheerful,
completely unaware of what's ahead.

33:39.809 --> 33:41.144
I like her.

33:45.857 --> 33:46.941
Then…

33:50.403 --> 33:52.155
I should try to be like her.

33:54.490 --> 33:55.616
I'll do that.

33:59.120 --> 34:00.079
I should go.

34:39.952 --> 34:41.954
[music ends]

35:02.100 --> 35:03.434
[breathes heavily]

35:19.450 --> 35:21.661
Eun-a, let's eat.

35:23.079 --> 35:27.125
[chuckling] It makes me so happy
to cook for you.

35:27.834 --> 35:29.877
I'm done. There's a lot of things
to do around here.

35:30.711 --> 35:32.338
What are you going to do today?

35:33.422 --> 35:34.757
I'm going to drop by my house.

35:35.591 --> 35:37.635
I just want to clean the kitchen.

35:39.095 --> 35:40.513
You're going to go inside?

35:42.640 --> 35:43.808
Just the kitchen.

35:45.768 --> 35:47.854
[chuckling] Okay, already.
I'll come visit.

35:50.523 --> 35:52.733
-Thanks for everything.
-All the best.

35:52.817 --> 35:54.152
It's been a pleasure.

36:23.639 --> 36:25.099
[line ringing]

36:29.896 --> 36:31.898
I thought this would be
an invalid number by now.

36:32.982 --> 36:35.776
<i>Dong-sik told me you're leaving Korea.</i>

36:36.527 --> 36:37.612
I'm leaving soon.

36:38.613 --> 36:41.699
[Seong-chan] <i>If you have something to say,</i>
<i>go ahead. I'm sure you resent me.</i>

36:53.711 --> 36:55.087
<i>I'm not really one to talk,</i>

36:55.880 --> 36:57.715
<i>but back then, I thought you'd abandoned</i>

36:57.798 --> 36:59.926
<i>the guesthouse you loved</i>
<i>because of that guy.</i>

37:00.509 --> 37:03.179
I was so angry,
wondering what my efforts were all for.

37:04.388 --> 37:06.515
<i>But once I'd calmed down…</i>

37:07.600 --> 37:08.684
[inhales] Back then--

37:08.768 --> 37:11.479
[Eun-a]
<i>I didn't plan to go there and meet him.</i>

37:11.562 --> 37:13.981
I really did run into him
by chance in Seoul.

37:16.609 --> 37:19.362
And I tried my best to bring
what I'd started to a proper close.

37:21.322 --> 37:23.032
<i>Not that you'd believe me.</i>

37:24.075 --> 37:25.660
Is that what you wanted to say?

37:27.536 --> 37:29.163
<i>To be fair, running into people happens.</i>

37:29.956 --> 37:31.582
<i>You remember the girl I went out with?</i>

37:31.666 --> 37:33.251
Your roommate during your intern days.

37:34.627 --> 37:36.087
I remember.

37:36.170 --> 37:39.215
She said how you looked
in your hotel uniform

37:39.298 --> 37:41.050
and in regular clothes
was really different.

37:41.634 --> 37:44.428
<i>She said you didn't look good</i>
<i>in regular clothes. It was ridiculous.</i>

37:44.512 --> 37:46.180
You said the same thing back then.

37:47.014 --> 37:49.600
<i>You said that excuse was ridiculous.</i>
[chuckles]

37:50.434 --> 37:53.562
<i>I ran into someone I dated in Gangneung</i>
<i>all the way in Geoje Island.</i>

37:54.480 --> 37:55.856
It does happen.

37:56.857 --> 37:58.276
<i>In all my life,</i>

37:58.359 --> 38:01.570
<i>you were the first person</i>
<i>who listened to me so attentively</i>

38:02.738 --> 38:05.032
and respected what I said.

38:05.825 --> 38:07.159
[gentle music playing]

38:07.243 --> 38:08.494
And I'm nobody special.

38:09.537 --> 38:11.706
<i>You're someone I care enough</i>
<i>to worry about.</i>

38:12.957 --> 38:15.293
<i>I'm relieved you're going to live</i>
<i>with Park So-hyeon.</i>

38:15.876 --> 38:19.088
When I left this job,
I was wondering why I felt so empty.

38:20.381 --> 38:22.383
It was because
you had been there at every step.

38:23.467 --> 38:25.761
<i>Without your feedback,</i>

38:25.845 --> 38:28.055
<i>I found myself without dreams or anything.</i>

38:28.139 --> 38:30.057
<i>I'd planned to just get by in life,</i>

38:31.851 --> 38:34.562
but I ended up pushing myself
to keep up with you.

38:36.022 --> 38:37.356
<i>For those ten years of my life…</i>

38:39.191 --> 38:41.402
only you know how hard I worked.

38:43.154 --> 38:44.905
I'll vouch for that.

38:45.781 --> 38:50.286
<i>I'll be the one to vouch</i>
<i>for how you gave it everything you had.</i>

38:51.287 --> 38:52.455
That's enough for me.

38:56.417 --> 38:57.835
Take care.

39:00.171 --> 39:01.172
[Eun-a] <i>You too.</i>

39:02.923 --> 39:06.927
Actually, saying goodbye
over the phone isn't so bad.

39:08.679 --> 39:09.930
Thank you,

39:11.682 --> 39:12.850
Seong-chan.

39:12.933 --> 39:14.185
[Seong-chan] <i>Thank you too.</i>

39:15.353 --> 39:16.187
<i>Bye.</i>

39:25.905 --> 39:27.907
[music continues playing]

39:29.909 --> 39:31.118
[Eun-a] Please come over here.

39:36.040 --> 39:38.334
Happy New Year.

39:40.086 --> 39:41.087
[chuckles awkwardly]

39:57.853 --> 39:59.146
[exclaims]

40:14.120 --> 40:16.122
[music fades]

40:48.946 --> 40:50.573
[dramatic music playing]

40:53.617 --> 40:57.288
HAPPY BIRTHDAY
NOVEMBER 9, 2024

41:19.977 --> 41:21.061
[sighs heavily]

41:27.318 --> 41:29.236
Is a half-open drawer

41:30.905 --> 41:32.281
really that big a deal?

41:34.658 --> 41:38.871
[sighing] Is this… [breathing heavily]

41:38.954 --> 41:41.040
Is this supposed to be…

41:42.458 --> 41:44.168
this painful?

41:46.754 --> 41:49.840
Dad can barely breathe,
as if he's running a marathon,

41:49.924 --> 41:51.842
and here you are complaining…

41:51.926 --> 41:53.177
[scoffs]

41:56.263 --> 41:57.264
[sighs]

42:02.311 --> 42:03.729
[line ringing]

42:05.189 --> 42:06.357
[Tae-seo]<i> I'm on my way.</i>

42:06.440 --> 42:07.483
No, it's fine.

42:08.400 --> 42:09.860
Let's not meet up today.

42:12.947 --> 42:14.156
[groans]

42:19.245 --> 42:20.538
[line ringing]

42:22.081 --> 42:23.415
[breath trembling]

42:24.833 --> 42:26.043
[frustrated sigh]

42:28.420 --> 42:30.256
Owner of car 2017?

42:39.848 --> 42:41.183
Owner of car 2017?

42:41.267 --> 42:43.894
-[banging on door]
-[A-sol] Hello? Anyone home?

42:43.978 --> 42:45.104
[banging on door]

42:45.688 --> 42:47.773
-[A-sol] Owner of car 2017?
-A-sol?

42:48.732 --> 42:49.942
[frustrated sigh]

42:50.025 --> 42:51.318
What's wrong?

42:52.111 --> 42:54.280
I need to get my car out,
but no one's answering.

42:56.323 --> 42:58.909
-[A-sol sighs heavily]
-[cellphone vibrating]

43:01.453 --> 43:03.747
Hi, Mom. I'm busy right now,
so I'll call you back…

43:05.332 --> 43:06.834
[somber music playing]

43:08.544 --> 43:09.587
Yeah.

43:10.337 --> 43:12.590
No, I'm not busy. I'll be right there.

43:14.258 --> 43:15.259
Mom, don't cry.

43:17.261 --> 43:18.304
Okay, bye.

43:21.724 --> 43:22.933
The car…

43:23.684 --> 43:25.102
Tell them to move it.

43:26.228 --> 43:29.148
I need to go to my dad right away.

43:32.151 --> 43:34.570
-[breath trembling]
-A-sol.

43:39.742 --> 43:41.744
[shuddering]

43:59.219 --> 44:00.220
[A-sol sighs]

44:03.223 --> 44:05.893
He's okay for now.

44:08.228 --> 44:11.690
My mom said he'll have bouts like this,
and then recover again,

44:11.774 --> 44:13.567
so she asked me to bring some clothes.

44:14.151 --> 44:15.402
Is there anything I can do?

44:16.236 --> 44:17.863
I left it at your house.

44:19.823 --> 44:21.158
But I wasn't expecting this.

44:22.076 --> 44:23.577
You'll see when you go home.

44:24.161 --> 44:27.206
I took it there
so you could work on it slowly,

44:29.124 --> 44:30.751
but I think you'll have to hurry.

44:33.545 --> 44:34.463
Okay.

44:35.547 --> 44:36.590
I'll get going.

44:37.841 --> 44:38.967
Tae-seo.

44:40.386 --> 44:41.804
A few days ago,

44:41.887 --> 44:43.681
that person with the bicycle…

44:46.058 --> 44:47.893
She came to your house.

44:49.144 --> 44:52.606
[exhales] All I had to do
was pick up my car,

44:52.690 --> 44:54.942
but I went up to your house like a fool

44:56.193 --> 44:57.403
and entered the passcode.

44:59.279 --> 45:01.448
When I went back down, she wasn't there.

45:02.032 --> 45:04.034
I must've been out of my mind.
[chuckles softly]

45:04.910 --> 45:05.994
[sighs]

45:10.582 --> 45:11.417
I'm sorry.

45:17.339 --> 45:18.257
[A-sol] Tae-seo.

45:19.675 --> 45:21.468
It's my turn to hear it.

45:24.012 --> 45:27.015
I really need to be ready now.
[inhales sharply]

45:27.099 --> 45:28.642
[voice breaking] I don't have…

45:30.144 --> 45:32.479
I don't have much time.

45:35.482 --> 45:38.527
Tell me what you want to thank me for

45:39.736 --> 45:40.988
right now.

45:41.905 --> 45:43.282
I want to hear it now.

45:47.369 --> 45:48.370
[sighs softly]

45:53.667 --> 45:56.462
Do you want to take a walk?

46:02.259 --> 46:04.261
[gentle music playing]

46:15.272 --> 46:16.273
[Tae-seo] The reason

46:17.774 --> 46:19.026
why I'm grateful to you is,

46:22.946 --> 46:24.198
thanks to you,

46:26.783 --> 46:28.911
I can now hope for a warm goodbye.

46:33.165 --> 46:34.291
As you know…

46:38.545 --> 46:39.546
[door closes]

46:39.630 --> 46:41.632
[music fades]

47:00.651 --> 47:02.653
[somber music playing]

47:18.085 --> 47:21.922
[A-sol]<i> If the three moments of waiting</i>
<i>that are needed to make a frame</i>

47:22.005 --> 47:23.882
<i>can all be done in a day…</i>

47:25.467 --> 47:27.761
-That thing I mentioned before…
-You mean my name tag?

47:28.470 --> 47:30.722
JULY 2014

47:30.806 --> 47:31.640
Thanks.

47:31.723 --> 47:34.226
MAEUM STUDY CENTER

47:37.604 --> 47:38.564
[A-sol]<i> …I'll believe</i>

47:40.065 --> 47:42.818
<i>that the sincere and heartfelt support</i>
<i>I gave you back then</i>

47:42.901 --> 47:47.531
<i>went around and found its way back to me.</i>

47:56.081 --> 47:58.458
<i>Please use </i>hanji<i> for the mat</i>

47:58.542 --> 48:00.377
<i>and oak for the frame.</i>

48:01.753 --> 48:05.716
<i>I want it to feel like my dad's face</i>
<i>is being warmly embraced.</i>

48:09.386 --> 48:10.429
<i>I'm counting on you.</i>

48:38.624 --> 48:40.626
[music fades]

48:44.087 --> 48:46.089
[Hwa-sun] The snow has let up.

48:51.219 --> 48:55.223
It seems it was snowing earlier
for your grandma.

48:57.142 --> 48:58.352
Ah…

49:00.228 --> 49:03.148
[Gyeong-chun] <i>Hui-seo's grandma's memory</i>
<i>keeps coming and going?</i>

49:03.815 --> 49:05.984
-They said her brain is still recovering.
-Hmm.

49:06.068 --> 49:09.071
For now, her memory will be mixed up,
but it'll come back again.

49:09.780 --> 49:10.614
Oh.

49:11.615 --> 49:15.994
[sighing] When you get old,
ten years ago feels like yesterday,

49:16.078 --> 49:18.622
and yesterday feels distant.

49:20.415 --> 49:21.792
Your mind is all over the place.

49:23.627 --> 49:24.961
[Gyeong-chun humming]

49:25.045 --> 49:27.089
Oh. They're coming.

49:51.655 --> 49:52.864
Where is she?

49:52.948 --> 49:54.991
I'm right here.

49:56.243 --> 49:57.369
Welcome back.

49:57.953 --> 49:59.162
-Mmm.
-[patting gently]

49:59.246 --> 50:00.288
Where's Eun-a?

50:00.372 --> 50:01.581
[Gyeong-chun] Hmm?

50:02.624 --> 50:04.710
Eun-a is from ten years ago.

50:04.793 --> 50:07.462
[Gyeong-chun] Mmm. Hwa-sun.

50:07.546 --> 50:09.715
What do you want with Eun-a? Hmm?

50:13.719 --> 50:15.345
[Gyeong-chun yelling in distance] Eun-a.

50:18.014 --> 50:19.891
Eun-a!

50:26.064 --> 50:27.149
Eun-a.

50:28.734 --> 50:30.193
Give me your hands.

50:30.277 --> 50:32.863
Gosh, you were clearing the snow.

50:32.946 --> 50:34.573
Are you all right?

50:37.409 --> 50:41.121
To her, today's the day
you cleared the snow.

50:42.998 --> 50:44.708
You think Tae-seo made it there, okay?

50:44.791 --> 50:47.085
Gosh, I don't know. I'm worried.

50:47.169 --> 50:50.088
[wind blowing]

50:50.172 --> 50:51.548
[Chang-sik exhales]

50:52.507 --> 50:55.010
[emotional music playing]

50:55.093 --> 50:58.513
[Hwa-sun]
<i>You cleared all the snow from our truck.</i>

50:59.222 --> 51:01.600
We had to send Tae-seo off
to the military all on his own.

51:02.476 --> 51:05.145
There was nothing we could do.

51:07.981 --> 51:09.733
Did it hurt?

51:11.902 --> 51:15.489
It hurt really badly,
but I'm all better now.

51:16.281 --> 51:17.824
That's good.

51:17.908 --> 51:19.743
Well done.

51:19.826 --> 51:21.328
I heard you're going to Hawaii.

51:22.078 --> 51:24.998
Oh… Have a safe trip.

51:25.081 --> 51:30.045
We'll check in on your dad often
so he doesn't feel too lonely.

51:31.463 --> 51:35.050
I meant to tell you this.
It's been weighing on my heart.

51:38.470 --> 51:40.472
Thank you.

51:49.439 --> 51:51.441
[music continues playing]

52:07.165 --> 52:08.208
[sighs]

52:10.627 --> 52:12.128
[cellphone vibrating]

52:14.589 --> 52:16.716
[music fades]

52:16.800 --> 52:17.801
Grandma?

52:19.052 --> 52:20.387
It's me, Tae-seo.

52:21.179 --> 52:22.472
You remember me, right?

52:22.556 --> 52:24.683
[Hwa-sun chuckling]
<i>Why wouldn't I remember you?</i>

52:25.517 --> 52:27.185
I'm back home safe and sound.

52:28.061 --> 52:29.062
[sighs in relief]

52:32.107 --> 52:34.568
-[loudly] Eun-a!
-[honking]

52:37.237 --> 52:39.072
[Hui-seo] My grandma's back.

52:39.155 --> 52:41.366
-Not from ten years ago. From right now.
-What?

52:42.576 --> 52:43.660
Get on.

52:43.743 --> 52:45.787
It's right now. The present!

52:45.871 --> 52:47.747
Yeah, I understand.

52:47.831 --> 52:51.418
[engine revs]

52:52.294 --> 52:55.297
[Hwa-sun] The Hangang River
has a lot of bridges, doesn't it?

52:55.380 --> 52:56.631
It's so long.

52:57.632 --> 52:58.675
You run there every day?

52:59.551 --> 53:02.429
[Tae-seo over phone] <i>I'm usually</i>
<i>sitting down when I'm operating trains,</i>

53:03.722 --> 53:06.016
<i>so it's a way for me to exercise.</i>

53:07.142 --> 53:08.143
Right. Good idea.

53:08.226 --> 53:11.021
You need to look after your health
while you work.

53:12.147 --> 53:13.440
<i>Goodness, Eun-a!</i>

53:14.107 --> 53:15.483
[Eun-a over phone] <i>How are you?</i>

53:15.567 --> 53:17.694
[gentle music playing]

53:17.777 --> 53:20.196
Eun-a. Gosh, Eun-a.

53:20.280 --> 53:21.573
Welcome back.

53:22.741 --> 53:24.951
<i>You haven't changed one bit.</i>

53:25.827 --> 53:27.787
[Eun-a] <i>You're the same as well.</i>

53:27.871 --> 53:31.374
-[Hwa-sun chuckling]
-[Eun-a]<i> I'll redo your scarf for you.</i>

53:33.001 --> 53:37.714
<i>Wrap it round and around, and then tie it.</i>

53:37.797 --> 53:39.132
<i>There. Nice and warm.</i>

53:39.215 --> 53:40.842
[Hwa-sun and Eun-a chuckling]

53:41.593 --> 53:45.013
[Hwa-sun]<i> Everyone here</i>
<i>worried about you so much.</i>

53:45.722 --> 53:48.433
<i>It's so good that you came back.</i>

53:48.516 --> 53:50.644
<i>-Well done.</i>
-[patting gently]

54:00.236 --> 54:02.238
[music fades]

54:04.908 --> 54:06.076
[cellphone vibrates]

54:13.875 --> 54:16.503
[Tae-seo] <i>I'll see you off tomorrow.</i>

54:17.420 --> 54:18.630
<i>Let's say goodbye in person.</i>

54:30.976 --> 54:32.268
-Granny.
-Yeah?

54:32.352 --> 54:34.020
You have to live well even without me.

54:34.688 --> 54:37.649
-It'll feel empty when I'm suddenly gone.
-[Gyeong-chun] You're right.

54:37.732 --> 54:39.901
It's been like a picnic lately,

54:39.985 --> 54:42.529
eating and sleeping together every day.

54:42.612 --> 54:44.698
But after a picnic,
you need to go live your life.

54:45.323 --> 54:47.784
You can't keep pining for it forever.

54:48.368 --> 54:49.619
You're right.

54:51.037 --> 54:52.122
[Gyeong-chun chuckles]

54:52.205 --> 54:54.207
[gentle music playing]

54:55.458 --> 54:56.876
Thanks, Granny.

54:56.960 --> 54:58.420
[Gyeong-chun chuckling]

55:03.091 --> 55:04.009
Let's take a photo.

55:04.092 --> 55:07.554
-A photo? [chuckles softly]
-Yeah. Photos look nicer with plants.

55:09.973 --> 55:10.974
[Gyeong-chun chuckling]

55:11.057 --> 55:13.435
-I'm going to look at this every day.
-[Gyeong-chun] Okay.

55:14.269 --> 55:16.104
Smile and say "Eun-a."

55:16.688 --> 55:19.524
Mo Eun-a.

55:19.607 --> 55:21.901
[laughing]

55:22.527 --> 55:24.029
-[chuckles]
-[camera shutter clicks]

55:24.112 --> 55:27.157
[Eun-a] So beautiful.
I'm going to look at this photo every day.

55:27.240 --> 55:28.575
[chuckles]

55:32.495 --> 55:34.497
[music continues playing]

55:52.557 --> 55:55.560
[Eun-a]<i> I'll come to Dongjak Station.</i>

56:00.607 --> 56:03.109
[Tae-seo]
<i>Dongjak Station to Incheon is too short.</i>

56:17.290 --> 56:18.708
[bus door hydraulics hissing]

56:28.301 --> 56:30.303
[music fades]

56:49.197 --> 56:51.199
[emotional music builds]

56:56.871 --> 56:58.873
[emotional music playing]

57:26.359 --> 57:27.193
[cellphone vibrates]

57:30.405 --> 57:31.448
YEON NAMSAN

57:36.286 --> 57:38.580
[Tae-seo]<i> These are the views</i>
<i>from my everyday routine.</i>

57:41.291 --> 57:42.625
<i>You wanted to see them too.</i>

57:59.142 --> 57:59.976
<i>I'm</i>…

58:01.519 --> 58:04.564
<i>going to do what we talked about together.</i>

58:06.816 --> 58:08.902
<i>You're the reason I could make up my mind,</i>

58:09.486 --> 58:11.196
<i>so I'll wait for you there.</i>

58:12.030 --> 58:17.118
<i>You should go there,</i>
<i>be loved and appreciated,</i>

58:17.202 --> 58:18.786
<i>and live a great life.</i>

58:19.621 --> 58:21.039
<i>And when you ever feel like</i>

58:21.706 --> 58:24.042
<i>thinking about a future that includes me,</i>

58:25.585 --> 58:26.836
<i>let me know.</i>

58:49.734 --> 58:51.736
[music ends]

58:53.363 --> 58:55.073
Let's say goodbye here.

59:05.208 --> 59:06.709
Thank you for seeing me off.

59:08.670 --> 59:09.504
This is…

59:11.297 --> 59:14.175
the first time we're saying
goodbye in person.

59:18.763 --> 59:19.931
Goodbye then.

59:20.014 --> 59:22.016
[melancholic music playing]

59:31.734 --> 59:33.111
Goodbye.

01:00:00.221 --> 01:00:01.514
I love you,

01:00:04.934 --> 01:00:05.893
Mo Eun-a.

01:00:30.627 --> 01:00:32.629
[music fades]

01:00:38.926 --> 01:00:42.305
Ladies and gentlemen, the next station is…

01:00:55.234 --> 01:00:57.695
Please take a moment
to look out the window.

01:01:06.788 --> 01:01:08.790
[gentle music playing]

01:01:14.754 --> 01:01:16.839
[Tae-seo]<i> An ordinary view from our lives</i>

01:01:18.841 --> 01:01:20.760
<i>may become an unforgettable brilliance</i>

01:01:22.470 --> 01:01:23.680
<i>that could lead you somewhere,</i>

01:01:26.057 --> 01:01:27.266
<i>somehow,</i>

01:01:28.476 --> 01:01:30.144
<i>and to someone.</i>

01:01:34.691 --> 01:01:36.067
<i>I hope that today</i>

01:01:36.150 --> 01:01:38.778
<i>was another meaningful day</i>

01:01:39.487 --> 01:01:41.948
<i>where you followed</i>
<i>the shining light within you.</i>

01:01:43.658 --> 01:01:44.701
<i>You did a wonderful job</i>

01:01:46.369 --> 01:01:47.954
<i>getting through the day.</i>

01:01:53.668 --> 01:01:55.420
The next station is…

01:02:05.471 --> 01:02:10.268
1 YEAR LATER

01:02:21.320 --> 01:02:23.322
[music fades]

01:02:36.669 --> 01:02:40.006
CHEONGGYEONG STATION

01:02:44.427 --> 01:02:45.845
[cellphone vibrates]

01:03:04.530 --> 01:03:06.532
[emotional music playing]

01:03:49.158 --> 01:03:56.123
MO EUN-A

01:04:37.123 --> 01:04:38.457
[Tae-seo] <i>Where we'll be…</i>

01:04:38.541 --> 01:04:39.917
[Eun-a] <i>Where we'll be…</i>

01:04:41.544 --> 01:04:44.255
-[Tae-seo] <i>What we'll be doing…</i>
-[Eun-a] <i>What we'll be doing…</i>

01:04:48.050 --> 01:04:50.428
-<i>And with who.</i>
-[Tae-seo]<i> And with who.</i>

01:04:50.511 --> 01:04:54.765
STILL SHINING

01:04:55.349 --> 01:04:58.769
STILL SHINING

01:04:58.853 --> 01:05:00.855
[music continues playing]

01:06:03.376 --> 01:06:05.378
Subtitle translation by: Hyesoo Lee
